        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 1:44PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 144 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Paris, moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Paris, Kansas, Vermilion, Redmon, and Oliver.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
